        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3743950471" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10829841708512729056">I purchased and read a different edition of the five poems of this unknown author from the fourteenth century in the mid-seventies as part of my continuing fascination with medieval literature. Translated, edited and with a very helpful introduction from Margaret Williams, my volume includes the work for which this writer is best known:  which tells one of the best male-vs-.female stories I&apos;ve ever read, complete with wit, suspense and true romance. As well, the poems , <i>Cleanness,</i>, <i>Pearl</i> and <i>Sai</i></span>
  <span id="freeText10829841708512729056" style="display:none">I purchased and read a different edition of the five poems of this unknown author from the fourteenth century in the mid-seventies as part of my continuing fascination with medieval literature. Translated, edited and with a very helpful introduction from Margaret Williams, my volume includes the work for which this writer is best known:  which tells one of the best male-vs-.female stories I've ever read, complete with wit, suspense and true romance. As well, the poems , <i>Cleanness,</i>, <i>Pearl</i> and <i>Saint Erkenwald</i> are included. I was quite appreciative of the translation, for my skills in Middle English are so weak as to <i>sikerly</i> drive me <i>wood</i>! <br /><br />Unfortunately, not well remembered after a quarter of a century.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10829841708512729056" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
