<div id="review_2485923388" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2485923388" />
    <a title="Ethan Campbell" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/84952814-ethan-campbell"><img alt="Ethan Campbell" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1533961327p2/84952814.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2485923388?book_show_action=true">Aug 07, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ethan Campbell" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ethan Campbell" href="/user/show/84952814-ethan-campbell">Ethan Campbell</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780859897266" href="/book/show/429581.Poems_of_the_Pearl_Manuscript">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2485923388" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6464970283953973205">The definitive edition of these classic 14th-century poems. Andrew &amp; Waldron preserve the original Middle English alphabet, including thorns and yoghs, but they use modern punctuation and capitalization to make the sentences easier to read. The most recent editions of this book include a CD-ROM of their prose translation, which is immensely helpful if you want do a serious study of these poems but aren&apos;t experienced in Middle English and/or don&apos;t want to spend hours wading through the glossary.</span>
  <span id="freeText6464970283953973205" style="display:none">The definitive edition of these classic 14th-century poems. Andrew &amp; Waldron preserve the original Middle English alphabet, including thorns and yoghs, but they use modern punctuation and capitalization to make the sentences easier to read. The most recent editions of this book include a CD-ROM of their prose translation, which is immensely helpful if you want do a serious study of these poems but aren't experienced in Middle English and/or don't want to spend hours wading through the glossary.</span>
  <a data-text-id="6464970283953973205" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


